   <Comment>Discrimination diagram for classifying altered volcanic island arc rocks. Classification field boundaries were constructed using composition data from island arc lavas.</Comment>
   <Comment>Th and Co on y- and x-axes are used as proxies for K2O and SiO2 respectively. Th is used to subdivide volcanic arc rocks into volcanic series: tholeiitic, calc-alkaline, high-K calc-alkaline and shoshonitic.</Comment>
